{"article_id":"G5dS42uL7w9qsgRC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi asked President Donald Trump to reschedule his State of the Union address this month","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"if the government remains shuttered","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"- or deliver it in writing .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"`` Sadly ,","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"given the security concerns","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"and unless government re-opens this week ,","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"I suggest","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that we work together","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"to determine another suitable date","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"after government has re-opened for this address","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"or for you to consider delivering your State of the Union address in writing to the Congress on January 29th , ''","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"Pelosi wrote in a letter to Trump on Wednesday .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"The partial government shutdown is in its 26th day , the longest in U.S. history .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Trump demanded $ 5.7 billion","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"to pay for a wall along the U.S.-Mexican border","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"and vowed to veto any legislation","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"that does not include the sum .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Democrats oppose a wall","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"and refuse to appropriate the money .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"The White House did not immediately respond to a request for comment from .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Pelosi cited Homeland Security Secretary Kirstjen Nielsen 's designation of State of the Union addresses as a `` National Special Security Event , ''","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"which requires a high level of security .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"The Secret Service is responsible for such events ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"but the agency , a part of the Department of Homeland Security , is affected by the shutdown .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"After sending the letter ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Pelosi said","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"the State of the Union requires hundreds of people to work out logistics and security ,","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"and most of them have been furloughed","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"or are working without pay","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"because of the shutdown .","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"Trump `` can make","depth":15},{"id":32,"text":"( the speech )","depth":15},{"id":33,"text":"from the Oval Office","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"if he wants , ''","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"she said .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"\" The Department of Homeland Security and the US Secret Service are fully prepared to support and secure the State of the Union , ''","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"she wrote on Twitter .","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"`` We thank the Service for their mission focus and dedication","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"and for all","depth":15},{"id":40,"text":"they do each day","depth":15},{"id":41,"text":"to secure our homeland . \"","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy said","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"Trump `` has a right ''","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"to give the speech","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"and that Americans `` have the right ''","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"to hear it .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Speaker Pelosi is playing politics","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"like I ' ve never seen a speaker before , ''","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"McCarthy said .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"`` I think","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"it ' s unbecoming of the office to disinvite the president . ''","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Written State of the Union-type addresses were once presidential practice .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"The nation 's first two presidents , George Washington and John Adams , delivered annual messages to Congress in person .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Successor Thomas Jefferson began submitting his in writing in 1801 , a routine","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that continued for more than a century .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"President Woodrow Wilson revived the practice of in-person speeches , his first coming in 1913 .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"The U.S. Constitution says","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"presidents \" shall from time to time give to the Congress Information of the State of the Union , '' remarks","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"formally known as the `` Annual Message '' for decades .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"President Franklin Roosevelt began describing the speeches as the `` state of the Union , '' a term","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"officially adopted in 1947 during Harry Truman 's administration .","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"The last president","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"to submit only a written State of the Union","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"was lame duck Jimmy Carter in January 1981 ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"four days before he left office .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"Trump met Wednesday at the White House with the Problem Solvers Caucus , a bipartisan group of House members ,","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"to discuss the shutdown .","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"The day before , a moderate group of House Democrats spurned Trump 's invitation to a White House luncheon ,","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"viewing it as an attempt","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"to bypass Pelosi","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"as Trump tries to win support for funding for the border wall .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"Seven Democrats were among the Problem Solvers","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"who met with Trump on Wednesday :","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"Reps. Josh Gottheimer of New Jersey , Thomas Suozzi of New York , Vicente Gonzalez of Texas , Anthony Brindisi of New York , Dean Phillips of Minnesota , Max Rose of New York and Abigail Spanberger of Virginia .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"`` Over the last weeks , we have been listening to our constituents","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"and speaking with our fellow members of Congress","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"- in both parties and in both chambers , ''","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"the Democrats said in a statement .","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"`` There is strong agreement across the aisle and around the country :","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"We must reopen the government .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"Our security , safety , and economy have been compromised ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"and millions of families are suffering . ''","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"The group said","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"there is strong agreement","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"that ``","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"if we reopen the government ,","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"the possibility exists","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"to work together","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"and find common ground","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"to tackle some of our country ' s toughest problems","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"and fix them .","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"But that conversation can only begin in earnest","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"once the government is reopened .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"We accepted the White House ' s invitation","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"to meet ...","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"to convey that message . ''","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"The names of Republican House members","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"who attended the meeting","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"have not been released .","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"White House spokeswoman Sarah Sanders said","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"Trump and his team had `` a constructive meeting '' with the bipartisan group .","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"\" They listened to one another ,","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"and now both have a good understanding","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"of what the other wants , ''","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"she said .","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"`` We look forward to more conversations like this . \"","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":215,"left":0,"right":214,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":214,"left":182,"right":213,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":173,"right":181,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":148,"right":172,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":148,"left":119,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":110,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":109,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":109,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":117,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":113,"right":116,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":113,"left":4,"right":112,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":112,"left":111,"right":7,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":111,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":116,"left":8,"right":115,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":114,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":114,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":13,"right":146,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":124,"right":145,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":122,"right":123,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":120,"right":121,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":120,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":20,"right":144,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":144,"left":127,"right":143,"rel